    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">Time to make a digit snake! You are given a string <var>n</var> made of digits <const>0-9</const> and an integer <var>c</var>.<br><br><strong>Steps:</strong><br><strong>1)</strong> Take the first <var>c</var> digits of the string <var>n</var>. If <var>c</var> calls for too many digits (i.e. <var>c</var> &gt; length of <var>n</var>), then just use the digits from <var>n</var> only.<br><strong>2)</strong> Split that substring into chunks of <const>8</const> digits. <br><strong>3)</strong> If the last chunk has less than <const>8</const> characters, fill in the gaps with <const>X</const>'s until the last chunk is <const>8</const> digits long.<br><strong>4)</strong> Print each chunk on a new line. Keep chunks at even indices <const>(0, 2, 4, ...)</const> as they are, but reverse chunks at odd indices <const>(1, 3, 5, ...)</const>.<br><br><strong>Example:</strong><br><var>n</var> = <const>1234567890987654321234567890</const><br><var>c</var> = <const>20</const><br><strong>1)</strong> First <var>c</var> digits of <var>n</var>: <const>12345678909876543212</const><br><strong>2)</strong> Split substring into chunks of <const>8</const>:<br><strong>Chunk 0:</strong> <const>12345678</const><br><strong>Chunk 1:</strong> <const>90987654</const><br><strong>Chunk 2:</strong> <const>3212</const><br><strong>3)</strong> Fill in the last chunk with <const>X</const>'s: <const>3212XXXX</const><br><strong>4)</strong> Print each chunk and reverse chunks at odd indices:<br><strong>Line 1:</strong> <const>12345678</const> <strong>(keep)</strong><br><strong>Line 2:</strong> <const>45678909</const> <strong>(reverse)</strong><br><strong>Line 3:</strong> <const>3212XXXX</const> <strong>(keep)</strong><br><br>Good luck!</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> A string <var>n</var> containing only digits <const>0-9</const>.<br><strong>Line 2:</strong> An integer <var>c</var> representing the number of digits to take from <var>n</var>.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\">The <strong>Digit Snake</strong> after executing the steps in the statement.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\"><const>1</const> &le; length of <var>n</var> &lt; <const>180</const><br><const>1</const> &le; <var>c</var> &le; <const>500</const></div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">1234567890987654321234567890\n20</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">12345678\n45678909\n3212XXXX</pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
